author: Austin White
title: Here are the former Oregon prep stars playing in 2025 women's March Madness - NewsBreak
text: The 2025 March Madness women’s NCAA tournament is here with 68 teams ready to battle for the national title. On six of those teams, basketball fans in Oregon can find some familiar names as former Beaver State prep stars are sprinkled throughout the field. Here’s a quick look at the nine former prepsters who are participating in the Big Dance on the women’s side and a look at how their season has gone. Tiara Bolden (Churchill HS), Oregon State, senior Played in 34 games with 30 starts.Averaged 8.2 points, 3.9 rebounds and 1.5 assists per game while shooting 37.7% from the field and 31.5% from deep.No. 14 Oregon State plays No. 3 North Carolina at 1:30 p.m. Saturday, March 22, on ESPNU. Aaronette Vonleh (West Linn HS), Baylor, senior Played and started in 34 games.Averaged a career high in points (14.6) and rebounds (5.6) per game in her first season at Baylor.Shot 57.3% from the floor and 65.7% from the free-throw line.No. 4 Baylor plays No. 13 Grand Canyon at 12:30 p.m. Friday, March 21, on ESPNU. Sydney Erikstrup (Beaverton HS), Grand Canyon, senior Played in 33 games.Averaged 2.8 points and 1.4 rebounds per game while shooting 36.7% from 3-point range.No. 13 Grand Canyon plays No. 4 Baylor at 12:30 p.m. Friday, March 21, on ESPNU. Laura Erikstrup (Beaverton HS), Grand Canyon, senior Played and started in 34 games.Averaged 14.4 points per game and her 7.1 rebounds per game leads the team.Shot 61.1% from the field and also averaged 1.4 steals per game.No. 13 Grand Canyon plays No. 4 Baylor at 12:30 p.m. Friday, March 21, on ESPNU. Donovyn Hunter (South Medford HS), TCU, sophomore Transferred from Oregon State to TCU.Played in 34 games with 17 starts.Averaged 5.6 points, 2.7 assists, 2.6 rebounds and 1.2 steals per game.No. 2 TCU plays No. 15 Fairleigh Dickinson a t 12:30 p.m. Friday, March 21, on ESPN2. Sofia Bell (St. Mary’s Academy/Jesuit HS), Oregon, sophomore Played in 26 games with 11 starts.Averaged 3.7 points and 1.5 rebounds per game.No. 10 Oregon plays No. 7 Vanderbilt at 2:30 p.m. Friday, March 21, on ESPNews. Kennedie Shuler (Barlow HS), Oregon State, sophomore Played and started 34 games.Averaged 7.9 points, 3.6 assists and 3.8 rebounds as the Beavers’ lead point guard.No. 14 Oregon State plays No. 3 North Carolina at 1:30 p.m. Saturday, March 22, on ESPNU. Ava Heiden (Sherwood HS), Iowa, freshman Played in 26 games.Averaged 4.7 points and 2.5 rebounds while shooting 55.4% from the field.Scored a career-high 11 points in the Big Ten tournament March 6 against Michigan State.No. 6 Iowa plays No. 11 Murray State at 9 a.m. Saturday, March 22, on ESPN. Ally Schimel (Corbett HS), Oregon State, freshman Played in 34 games with two starts.Averaged 3.5 points and 1.6 rebounds per game while shooting 28.4% from deep.No. 14 Oregon State plays No. 3 North Carolina at 1:30 p.m. Saturday, March 22, on ESPNU.
